## 2026-03-29 - Type scale preview is the weakest of all generators
- Replaced the "Ag" clamped (8–32px) preview with a two-section layout: (1) a scale ruler showing proportional horizontal bars with step name, token value → px, and ratio-to-previous-step labels; (2) a typography specimen with contextual text labels ("Display", "Heading", "Subheading", "Body text", etc.) rendered at actual sizes (capped at 52px to prevent extreme overflow). Both sections sort steps largest-to-smallest to emphasize hierarchy. The `formatValue() → Npx` annotation appears in both sections.
- Also fixed a pre-existing lint violation in `TokenGeneratorDialog.tsx` where two `useState` hooks were declared after an early `return` block, causing "hooks called conditionally" errors that bumped lint count from 3 to 5.
- Files changed: `packages/figma-plugin/src/ui/components/generators/TypeScaleGenerator.tsx` ~L89-112, `packages/figma-plugin/src/ui/components/TokenGeneratorDialog.tsx` ~L216-403

